oretically use other OSS products. For someone working with Nablarch, this context matters when considering questions about framework flexibility or whether NAF is truly required. I'll flag this as a minor omission worth noting.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":17526,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":17526,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea9f416c-59a2-40f1-80ce-0b1db2cc62f1","uuid":"c5dd412f-990f-4c7d-abc1-32d56cb7fd18"}
